                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/174.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Bevan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Carrancista officers at Ebano, expecting attack, threaten to burn all wells and
                    stores to prevent Villistas obtaining fuel in case of defeat. Commander in
                    Tampico not very forcible in his denial that this is contemplated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bevan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
